<TITLE> HANS to hold annual autism programme </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 28 (bdnews24.com) - Student-run voluntary organisation, HANS, is set to hold its third annual event with a view to educating the public about the talent and intelligence of autistic children. The programme will be held on Nov 1 at the BIAM auditorium under the banner "Share with Innocence-III". The programme will be supported by Rahimafrooz (Bangladesh) Ltd, with media partners bdnews24.com, Channel I and Radio Foorti. The third issue of 'Reflection', a publication on autism, will also be published on the day. Students of HANS visit schools of autistic children all the year round, and once a year brings all the schools under one roof where the children participate in a cultural programme with an open discussion by the experts. As in previous years, this year's programme will include song, dance, poetry, a fashion show, story telling and theatre by the students of six special schools in Dhaka  AWF, Beautiful Mind, Caring Glory, Kallyani, SGC and SWAC. Abu Mohammad Moniruzzamn Khan, secretary of the land ministry will be the chief guest and professor Muhammad Zafar Iqbal and novelist Anisul Hoque among others will attend as special guests. Principles, teachers and guardians of the schools will also be present. bdnews
